The previous fuel prices retailed at Sh106.82 for Super Petrol, Sh91.82 for Diesel and Sh83.56 for Kerosene in Nairobi.The prices are inclusive of the 8 percent Value Added Tax (VAT) in line with provisions of the Finance Act. Motorists will have to dig deeper into their pockets after the Energy and Petroleum Regulatory Authority (EPRA) announced higher prices for the next 30 days.
In a press release, EPRA said that the prices of Super Petrol, Diesel and Kerosene will increase by Sh0.17, Sh4.57 and Sh3.56 per litre respectively in the new prices.



